I was gonna make a big review post for the new Where Kitsune Wait update, but it’s rather uninteresting, so I haven’t got much to say about it. Besides a few awkward lines that are either oddly worded or repetitive. I’ll show a few (albeit nitpicky) examples:
>I think I should offer the pots to Hibiki
I find it difficult to describe what makes this specific line so odd to me, but it just felt out of place for Egil in that moment. Maybe make it more active and not just a thought? Like he begins moving to Hibiki but Yuuko intervenes. Or make him not want to be near Hibiki, which is something I think is more believable.
>The four tailed Yuuko
I can understand this wording as an introduction to the character, but this is after she was referred to as simply Yuuko multiple times.
But that’s just small stuff. Otherwise, it feels like this is more of a build-up chapter than anything else. One last thing, I do like Egil’s interactions with most of the village kitsune, and I think them trying to get close to Egil could make for some fun dialogue, which was shown a bit in the dinner scene.

Some errors:
>and Setsuko hundreds of li away.
>She hasn't shown interest in me beyond what I can doto help and as a gracious host
